  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>First draft, online at <a href="http://openetherpad.org/calendar-events">http://openetherpad.org/calendar-events</a>

Pasting it here:


Q. What kinds of events should go on the OpenHatch calendar?

A. We want to promote events that directly bring new contributors into free 
software, or teach background needed to participate in free software projects. We 
only list events that are free-of-cost or reasonably inexpensive to attend. They 
can be in person or online.

To us, there is a grey area where some events teach how to use proprietary 
software. If those events are free of cost and explicitly about helping users 
contribute to free software, then they can go on the calendar, too. For all these 
events, it's fine if there is a cap to the maximum number of attendees. We'd 
appreciate if you could update the OpenHatch calendar when the event fills up.

To give you ideas, here are a few types of events we like:

Online ,"Open house" events, like Debian's "One day with Debian Perl Team" on 
July 1, 2011 &lt;<a href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-perl/2011/07/msg00002.html">http://lists.debian.org/debian-perl/2011/07/msg00002.html</a>&gt;
Diversity outreach events for in-person programming meetups, like the Boston 
Python Workshop that OpenHatch co-organizes 
&lt;<a href="http://openhatch.org/wiki/Boston_Python_Workshop_3">http://openhatch.org/wiki/Boston_Python_Workshop_3</a>&gt;
Parties to get newcomers involved in a free software project, like the Debian Bug 
Squashing Party held at MIT in December 2008 &lt;<a href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-">http://lists.debian.org/debian-</a>
devel/2008/12/<a href="msg00513">msg00513</a>.html&gt;
Periodic meetings that are open to new contributors, like P2PU's weekly code 
status meetings: <a href="https://github.com/p2pu/lernanta/wiki/Dev-Meetings-2011">https://github.com/p2pu/lernanta/wiki/Dev-Meetings-2011</a>
(Theoretically) A free-of-cost hack fest that teaches how to use Adobe 
Illustrator to design logos for free software projects.

We're not particularly interested in events that simply teach how to use free 
software. To qualify, you have to be teaching skills needed in free software 
contribution (like programming) or directly getting people involved.</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
